1
00:00:00,813 --> 00:00:05,375
I wasn't the one speaking.
It was the Universe.

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:08,135
The seventh year is exactly
when people break up.

3
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:10,905
The Universe has been screaming
until it's blue in the face.

4
00:00:10,930 --> 00:00:12,080
You still don't believe it?

5
00:00:13,134 --> 00:00:15,282
We promoted the heck out of it
and it still flopped.

6
00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:18,135
Stop clinging to the old style.

7
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:20,000
You need to open a new door.
Find a new angle.

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,920
I don't believe it. Not listening.
I don't want to know anything.

9
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:24,495
I don't want to know anymore.

10
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:26,100
I'm just tired!

11
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:29,040
Work is crazy busy.
I come home and I'm drained.

12
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,775
I'm tired too!

13
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,466
But I feel like
I'm the only one trying.

14
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,400
"Are you all asleep yet?"

15
00:00:44,398 --> 00:00:45,840
"I want to sleep too."

16
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:48,800
"But I can't sleep. I just can't."

17
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:51,640
"Because I want to change my life."

18
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:39,222
- Babe?
- Huh?

19
00:01:39,247 --> 00:01:41,735
It's late. Why aren't you sleeping?

20
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:43,960
Was I too loud? Did I wake you?

21
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,160
Sorry, sorry.

22
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:47,200
Mmm.

23
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:50,375
I'm just double-checking
the additional documents.

24
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,753
Just a sec.
I'll go to sleep soon.

25
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:53,880
Oh boy.

26
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,975
You're working too hard.

27
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,640
You're going to get Panda eyes.
You'll age prematurely.

28
00:02:03,298 --> 00:02:05,440
What Panda?
I'm using a face mask right now.

29
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,520
Working hard now is better than
not getting to be with you later.

30
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,480
- Hmm?
- Mmm.

31
00:02:13,129 --> 00:02:14,280
- You sleep.
- Mmm.

32
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,160
Okay? Good night.

33
00:02:16,684 --> 00:02:17,684
Good night.

34
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:18,950
Good night.

35
00:02:19,824 --> 00:02:22,648
Don't forget to turn off the light.

36
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,760
Okay...

37
00:02:32,758 --> 00:02:35,040
Here. Hot porridge.

38
00:02:35,065 --> 00:02:36,111
Ooh.

39
00:02:36,157 --> 00:02:37,840
Not sure if it's good, though.

40
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:41,200
I combined recipes from
several social media clips.

41
00:02:43,736 --> 00:02:45,240
Wow.

42
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,840
It's delicious.

43
00:02:49,482 --> 00:02:50,960
Very refreshing.

44
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,920
Very clean.

45
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,760
It really cleanses out the system.

46
00:02:56,760 --> 00:03:00,640
It's light, you know?
Like a thick oat porridge.

47
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:03,120
And this soft-boiled egg
is cooked perfectly.

48
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:06,720
If you praise me any more,
I'm going to float away.

49
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,046
Seriously.

50
00:03:08,071 --> 00:03:12,880
You're going to the gym later.
You need a substantial breakfast.

51
00:03:12,905 --> 00:03:13,905
Mmm.

52
00:03:14,133 --> 00:03:16,320
Mmm-hmm.

53
00:03:17,433 --> 00:03:19,320
Ohn, do you know...

54
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:22,440
what Japanese people
like to eat for breakfast?

55
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,680
Hmm...

56
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:28,617
Probably...

57
00:03:29,663 --> 00:03:31,600
Hot steamed rice?

58
00:03:31,624 --> 00:03:32,906
With miso soup.

59
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:36,560
Served with salt-grilled fish.

60
00:03:37,273 --> 00:03:39,953
Pickles and seaweed too.

61
00:03:39,953 --> 00:03:43,240
French breakfasts are
pretty minimal as well.

62
00:03:44,299 --> 00:03:46,040
Just a croissant and coffee.

63
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:50,680
That's true.
But would that be enough for you?

64
00:03:53,215 --> 00:03:54,411
Thailand, though...

65
00:03:55,208 --> 00:03:57,200
We have so many things to eat.

66
00:03:57,767 --> 00:04:01,655
Like in the morning,
you gotta have Patong-go
(Chinese fried dough)

67
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,781
Grilled pork and sticky rice.

68
00:04:03,806 --> 00:04:04,806
Porridge.

69
00:04:04,831 --> 00:04:08,303
Or even pork blood soup with rice.

70
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:12,720
So much delicious food here.

71
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,480
Filling and yummy.

72
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:21,613
But you know, Thai restaurants are
popping up all over the world now.

73
00:04:21,638 --> 00:04:22,638
Mmm.

74
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:27,600
If we moved to a nearby country,
that would be interesting.

75
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:30,920
Want to go to Singapore?

76
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,120
Hey, let's go, Jee!

77
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,735
- Seriously.
- Hmm.

78
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:39,459
We haven't traveled anywhere,
just the two of us, in a long time.

79
00:04:39,489 --> 00:04:40,536
- Mmm.
- Let's go!

80
00:04:41,045 --> 00:04:42,118
Mmm.

81
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,539
- But we wouldn't just be going--
- Oh, right...

82
00:04:46,015 --> 00:04:47,495
Did I tell you yet?

83
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,360
Chon and Nidnoi are planning

84
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:52,335
to get married before
they move to Canada.

85
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,400
Get married?

86
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,400
Mmm.

87
00:04:55,321 --> 00:04:57,560
I never really thought about that.
Get married?

88
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,280
But we're happy right now.

89
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:04,120
I mean, we are really happy.

90
00:05:04,368 --> 00:05:06,880
Come on, Jee. Don't overthink it.

91
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,840
Honestly, Ohn...

92
00:05:17,168 --> 00:05:18,520
No, this is good.

93
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,440
Let's get back to Singapore.

94
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,840
Do you remember Mr. Tony?

95
00:05:29,127 --> 00:05:30,560
- Tony?
- Mmm-hmm.

96
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,520
Tony Pink Zipper?

97
00:05:33,069 --> 00:05:36,120
That's the one. He came back
as a client for our company

98
00:05:36,292 --> 00:05:37,840
because of that
Pink Zipper campaign.

99
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,640
It was a huge hit.
Sold out completely.

100
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,711
- Really?
- Mmm.

101
00:05:41,736 --> 00:05:43,640
They launched it
right during Pink Dot.

102
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:47,451
Ah, Pink Dot.

103
00:05:47,476 --> 00:05:48,640
I do remember.

104
00:05:59,469 --> 00:06:00,520
So here's the thing...

105
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:04,690
Mr. Tony's company offered...

106
00:06:05,581 --> 00:06:08,321
They invited me to be
a Marketing Consultant

107
00:06:08,345 --> 00:06:11,107
at the Main Office in Singapore.

108
00:06:14,378 --> 00:06:15,378
Come with me.

109
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,200
Go where?

110
00:06:20,201 --> 00:06:21,321
To live in Singapore.

111
00:06:31,619 --> 00:06:33,200
Kick. Kick.

112
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,200
Hips. Use your hips.
Put your weight into it.

113
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,345
Again. Again.

114
00:06:38,713 --> 00:06:41,800
Okay, stop. Breathe.

115
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,040
You okay? You good?

116
00:06:45,813 --> 00:06:47,960
"This is A. The determined one."

117
00:06:48,321 --> 00:06:50,880
"My junior from university."

118
00:06:51,274 --> 00:06:53,749
"He is serious about everything."

119
00:06:53,774 --> 00:06:55,447
"Especially his image."

120
00:06:55,472 --> 00:06:57,712
"Right now, he needs to get fit"

121
00:06:57,736 --> 00:06:59,871
"because he has a challenge
with his boyfriend, Job."

122
00:07:00,222 --> 00:07:01,981
"He has to look better"

123
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:04,741
"like one of those models
on the thirst-trap apps."

124
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,255
Singapore? That's awesome.

125
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,628
I wanna go too. So jealous.

126
00:07:11,784 --> 00:07:14,055
Don't exaggerate, Mr. A.

127
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:17,440
Why would a high-earning auditor
like you be jealous of me?

128
00:07:17,465 --> 00:07:21,480
Oh come on. Sometimes you want
a change of scenery, you know?

129
00:07:21,505 --> 00:07:22,505
Mmm...

130
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,160
When would you go?

131
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,840
It's still under consideration.

132
00:07:29,403 --> 00:07:30,403
Mmm-hmm.

133
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,360
And what about Ohn?
What did he say?

134
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:43,840
Well, if I go start
a new job over there,

135
00:07:43,865 --> 00:07:46,135
I can extend my career

136
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,095
and work another 10 years
before retiring.

137
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,980
And if we live in Singapore,
you can still write your comics.

138
00:07:51,005 --> 00:07:54,720
A change of scenery and atmosphere.
You might find fresh ideas.

139
00:07:56,819 --> 00:07:57,859
Come with me, okay?

140
00:08:00,795 --> 00:08:05,760
About the job, I'm happy for you.

141
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,200
As for traveling, I want to go.

142
00:08:09,225 --> 00:08:10,259
Mmm.

143
00:08:10,259 --> 00:08:13,255
But this move is permanently.

144
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:16,000
And you sprung this on me
all of a sudden.

145
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,982
- I...
- Don't want to go.

146
00:08:19,744 --> 00:08:23,887
Jee, it's not that
I don't want to go.

147
00:08:24,723 --> 00:08:28,403
But I can't say that
I want to go either.

148
00:08:30,109 --> 00:08:33,296
Your question is
a closed-ended question.

149
00:08:33,296 --> 00:08:36,920
"Will you go? Won't you go?"
Ugh, it's hard to answer!

150
00:08:37,507 --> 00:08:39,000
Why do you have to get annoyed?

151
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,415
I'm not annoyed!

152
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,700
That right there is annoyance.

153
00:08:42,346 --> 00:08:44,120
I just asked you directly.

154
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:47,200
If I move to Singapore,
will you come live with me?

155
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:52,032
You can sleep on it.
Is that okay?

156
00:08:52,057 --> 00:08:54,480
Good. I need to think about it.

157
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,240
Mmm.

158
00:08:59,779 --> 00:09:00,942
Uh...

159
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,116
Today is Kit's anniversary.
I'll be home late.

160
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:08,667
Mmm-hmm.

161
00:09:15,253 --> 00:09:16,267
Come on, guys!

162
00:09:16,292 --> 00:09:17,918
- Spectrum Fabulous!
- Spectrum Fabulous!

163
00:09:17,943 --> 00:09:19,320
- Woo!
- Woo!

164
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,840
"We have come a long way."

165
00:09:22,224 --> 00:09:24,040
"This is Team Spectrum Fabulous."

166
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,600
"The name has no literal meaning."

167
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:29,111
"But it translates roughly to:
Diverse Wonders."

168
00:09:29,136 --> 00:09:31,240
"A legendary high school
volleyball team"

169
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,304
"with fabulous skills
at a high school level."

170
00:09:35,049 --> 00:09:38,320
"This is Chon.
Nickname: Chon the Dam Buster."

171
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:41,032
"Former Outside Hitter."

172
00:09:41,057 --> 00:09:42,760
"With a heavy spike."

173
00:09:42,784 --> 00:09:44,778
"Hitting hard, smashing every ball"

174
00:09:44,803 --> 00:09:46,707
"Piercing through
until the floor cracks."

175
00:09:46,732 --> 00:09:48,592
"Currently a Tattoo Artist."

176
00:09:48,617 --> 00:09:51,477
"Chon, Tattoo Artist"

177
00:09:52,135 --> 00:09:54,834
"This is Thai.
Former Middle Blocker."

178
00:09:54,859 --> 00:09:56,560
"Sweet-faced center blocker."

179
00:09:56,585 --> 00:09:58,600
- "Good voice, good looks."
- Yes!

180
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:00,366
"So he had to become
a professional singer."

181
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:03,595
"Currently transitioned to become
a Senior Music Director"

182
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:05,546
"for a media
entertainment company."

183
00:10:05,570 --> 00:10:06,613
"Thai"

184
00:10:07,809 --> 00:10:12,141
"And as for me, Ohn.
Former Libero."

185
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,375
"Nickname: Ohn-Libero."

186
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,701
"The name means
'Free Receiver,' but..."

187
00:10:16,726 --> 00:10:19,455
"Forbidden from the front zone,
setting or attacking above the net"

188
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,760
"Ohn-Libero's main duty was"

189
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:24,200
"do whatever it takes
to keep the ball off the floor."

190
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,760
"Be sticky. Be tough.
Like a stubborn stain."

191
00:10:27,481 --> 00:10:29,760
"Currently an obsolete
comic book artist."

192
00:10:30,317 --> 00:10:33,047
"Ohn, a comic book artist"

193
00:10:33,072 --> 00:10:35,877
- Come on, 1, 2, 3. Give me life!
- "And that..."

194
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:39,227
"Nidnoi. She's a nurse.
She wasn't on the team."

195
00:10:39,252 --> 00:10:41,895
"We met her later
because she's Chon's girlfriend."

196
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:44,335
"Ms. Chon's girlfriend,
the Ultimate Queer Queen."

197
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,160
"But let's save
their story for later"

198
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,330
"because today
the main character is"

199
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:53,096
"Kit, the Eternal Benchwarmer."

200
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:56,207
"Even when the coach
let him play, he refused."

201
00:10:56,232 --> 00:10:58,160
"He just wanted
to be with friends."

202
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,954
- Ready?
- "And we're here every year."

203
00:11:00,979 --> 00:11:04,280
"to make merit for Kit
who left us before his time."

204
00:11:07,463 --> 00:11:09,094
Here you go.

205
00:11:09,118 --> 00:11:11,261
Omelet on rice, your favorite.

206
00:11:11,286 --> 00:11:14,320
Here are some birth control pills.

207
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:19,280
They're easier to find now.
Lots of options too.

208
00:11:20,408 --> 00:11:24,000
Kit, remember, don't come visit us.

209
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:28,680
We'll visit you.
Don't think we'll forget.

210
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:33,320
As long as we're alive,
we'll visit you every year.

211
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:35,890
- Hey, Chon.
- Hmm?

212
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:38,760
You and Nidnoi are
moving abroad soon.

213
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,129
Making promises like that,

214
00:11:41,153 --> 00:11:43,303
it's going to be
a burden on me and Ohn.

215
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:45,244
- Hey.
- Well...

216
00:11:45,269 --> 00:11:46,360
Actually...

217
00:11:47,930 --> 00:11:50,455
I might move abroad too.

218
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,480
- Hmm?
- Hmm?

219
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:53,745
Mmm.

220
00:11:59,445 --> 00:12:01,116
I need to pee so bad.

221
00:12:01,141 --> 00:12:02,141
Right here.

222
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:05,120
- So many people.
- Long queue.

223
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,720
This side is totally empty!

224
00:12:07,745 --> 00:12:08,745
Come on.

225
00:12:09,296 --> 00:12:11,800
Thai, wait for me when you're done.

226
00:12:12,526 --> 00:12:13,600
- Mmm.
- Okay.

227
00:12:16,971 --> 00:12:18,011
I need to pee.

228
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,640
Actually, I'm good.
I'll go wait with Ohn.

229
00:12:39,587 --> 00:12:41,000
Bless you.

230
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:48,800
- Hey, Chon.
- Huh?

231
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:49,960
Done with the restroom?

232
00:12:50,281 --> 00:12:51,281
Too crowded.

233
00:12:55,199 --> 00:12:56,199
Chon...

234
00:12:56,613 --> 00:12:57,760
I know you.

235
00:12:58,463 --> 00:13:02,606
You're overthinking it. Just go in.
Holding it in isn't good for you.

236
00:13:03,192 --> 00:13:06,495
I didn't need to go that bad.
Just walking Nidnoi there.

237
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,815
Let the aunties
and grandmas go first.

238
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:12,415
Never thought I'd hear those words

239
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:16,120
coming from the mouth
of Chon the Dam Buster.

240
00:13:18,108 --> 00:13:21,135
Well, we grew up, didn't we?

241
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:22,681
Actually, we're old now.

242
00:13:22,706 --> 00:13:24,767
I can't be throwing a tantrum
like when I was young

243
00:13:24,792 --> 00:13:27,193
every time I used the restroom
and people stared,

244
00:13:27,218 --> 00:13:29,783
thinking they weren't
accepting me and bullying me.

245
00:13:31,228 --> 00:13:35,176
Maybe, they just don't feel safe.

246
00:13:35,864 --> 00:13:39,296
They aren't sure
if we are on their side.

247
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:45,375
Or maybe, they think I'm just
some pervert man in disguise.

248
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,440
Mmm.

249
00:13:47,479 --> 00:13:50,640
You've changed a lot
because of Nidnoi too, right?

250
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:55,680
You've changed because of Jee too.

251
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,202
Me? Changed?

252
00:13:58,227 --> 00:14:01,400
Please, I'm still totally myself.

253
00:14:01,425 --> 00:14:05,298
Stable and solid,
with the same ideology as always.

254
00:14:05,323 --> 00:14:09,326
Yet you're moving to
follow Jee to Singapore?

255
00:14:09,351 --> 00:14:10,928
You used to say,

256
00:14:10,952 --> 00:14:14,670
no matter what happens,
you'd die on Thai soil

257
00:14:14,695 --> 00:14:16,502
because you couldn't
stay away from Som Tum,

258
00:14:16,526 --> 00:14:19,187
your mom, your sister,
and your nephew.

259
00:14:19,212 --> 00:14:20,440
Hello?

260
00:14:26,008 --> 00:14:27,843
If you really follow Jee there,

261
00:14:29,147 --> 00:14:31,370
you better prepare yourself.

262
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:35,039
Prepare for what?

263
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:38,256
In case you guys break up.

264
00:14:43,274 --> 00:14:46,103
- Miss Chonticha.
- Yes?

265
00:14:46,438 --> 00:14:47,520
Come on, let's go.

266
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:48,840
- Okay, okay.
- Let's go.

267
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,560
We're heading off now.

268
00:14:52,301 --> 00:14:54,000
- Bye bye.
- Not yet? Sawasdee ka.

269
00:14:54,025 --> 00:14:55,480
- See you later.
- See ya.

270
00:14:58,997 --> 00:15:01,450
They're so cute, right?

271
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:04,490
What?

272
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,960
Well, Chon and Noi...

273
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,440
They take such good care
of each other. It's cute.

274
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:16,455
By the way, what I said earlier?
Did you even understand it?

275
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,616
Uh-uh.

276
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:21,095
Ohn, hasn't your English improved?

277
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,223
And you're going to
move to Singapore?

278
00:15:23,247 --> 00:15:24,580
Are you going to survive?

279
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Let's go home.

280
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:32,840
Come on! Don't just stand there.

281
00:15:33,716 --> 00:15:36,441
I'm trying to figure out

282
00:15:36,466 --> 00:15:39,015
what exactly you meant earlier.

283
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,040
Oh, geez.

284
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:43,920
What is wrong with you?

285
00:15:46,157 --> 00:15:48,663
- Yay!
- Yay!

286
00:15:49,465 --> 00:15:51,400
Congratulations, Tui.

287
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,895
- Finally getting to take a break.
- Finally off. Yes.

288
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:56,411
- Please, blow out the candles.
- Okay...

289
00:15:56,436 --> 00:15:58,600
- Go ahead.
- Blow them!

290
00:15:59,484 --> 00:16:01,484
- Wow.
- Wow.

291
00:16:02,397 --> 00:16:05,120
Alright, photo time everyone!
Come take a picture.

292
00:16:05,959 --> 00:16:08,360
- Excuse me, put this on.
- Go ahead.

293
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:09,981
There.

294
00:16:10,006 --> 00:16:11,240
Take care of the company.

295
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,960
My pleasure. Don't you worry.

296
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:16,720
- Sales will be booming!
- Thank you.

297
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,480
- Everyone look at the camera.
- Here we go.

298
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:21,240
Okay. 1, 2, 3!

299
00:16:23,385 --> 00:16:25,280
- Change pose!
- New pose!

300
00:16:25,305 --> 00:16:26,440
Like pose. Thumbs up.

301
00:16:29,940 --> 00:16:31,200
Jira.

302
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:32,225
Hmm?

303
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,440
Retirement cake.

304
00:16:41,464 --> 00:16:42,477
Hmm...

305
00:16:42,901 --> 00:16:45,680
Oh. Thank you very much, Jamie.
I was just about to go get some.

306
00:16:46,653 --> 00:16:47,960
My pleasure.

307
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:52,240
You have about 5 years left, right?

308
00:16:52,481 --> 00:16:53,593
Hmm?

309
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:56,040
I mean, work for another 5 years

310
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:58,406
and you'll be retiring too, right?

311
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:03,080
"Jamie, you presumptuous man."

312
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,680
Probably.

313
00:17:05,991 --> 00:17:07,520
I've never really counted.

314
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,724
I've been too focused on working.

315
00:17:09,749 --> 00:17:12,072
Thanks a lot, Jamie.

316
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,826
- Thank you.
- Sure thing.

317
00:17:14,149 --> 00:17:16,710
I'm actually really rooting for it.

318
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:21,360
I wonder if I'll take your place
when you're gone.

319
00:17:22,024 --> 00:17:23,160
Fingers crossed.

320
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:26,160
I probably won't be gone
that easily, Jamie.

321
00:17:26,185 --> 00:17:28,600
- Oh, really?
- Keep at it, though.

322
00:17:29,704 --> 00:17:30,760
Thank you.

323
00:17:31,082 --> 00:17:32,440
I need to get back to work now.

324
00:17:39,241 --> 00:17:40,720
Welcome back, Tony.

325
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:51,320
Ugh!

326
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,400
Too hard.

327
00:17:59,575 --> 00:18:00,855
"All English courses"

328
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:04,320
Which course should I take?
There are so many, I can't choose.

329
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,720
I can't do this. No way.

330
00:18:23,036 --> 00:18:26,000
They all cost money.

331
00:18:26,735 --> 00:18:29,600
Make money first, Ohn.
Make money first.

332
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:31,795
Come on... Come on...

333
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:32,820
Come on!

334
00:19:44,534 --> 00:19:49,224
"If I leave the Himmapan Forest,
everything I have now will vanish."

335
00:19:49,249 --> 00:19:52,284
"The magic, this body,
and these friends."

336
00:19:52,781 --> 00:19:54,581
"Oh no! Quack quack!"

337
00:19:54,605 --> 00:19:57,287
"Kittima is leaving the Forest!
Quack quack!"

338
00:19:57,311 --> 00:20:00,444
"Then who will help us
defeat Witch Laila?"

339
00:20:00,468 --> 00:20:03,217
"If she regains her powers,
what will we do?"

340
00:20:03,241 --> 00:20:05,554
"Quack quack! What do we do?
Can I go with you, Kittima?!"

341
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,520
Hey, Jee.

342
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,200
Did I scare you?

343
00:20:24,299 --> 00:20:25,299
Jee.

344
00:20:26,352 --> 00:20:27,392
Just got back?

345
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:28,767
Mmm.

346
00:20:28,791 --> 00:20:30,260
I stayed to clear up some work.

347
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:33,200
Did you eat yet?

348
00:20:34,129 --> 00:20:35,384
I ate already.

349
00:20:35,408 --> 00:20:37,408
What about you? Did you eat?

350
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:41,160
It's this late. I'll just skip it.

351
00:20:41,951 --> 00:20:45,120
Good idea. I can lose some weight.

352
00:20:45,327 --> 00:20:46,327
Hmm...

353
00:20:56,883 --> 00:20:58,640
Well, I guess I am hungry.

354
00:21:00,298 --> 00:21:02,844
Are you okay? That was loud.

355
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,120
Hold the elevator, please!

356
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:10,626
Ah... Thank you.

357
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:23,880
Absolutely not.

358
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,760
You have a blood test tomorrow.

359
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,440
Absolutely no eating.

360
00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:30,826
Can't I just have
one piece of chocolate?

361
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,400
No.

362
00:21:32,425 --> 00:21:34,425
You can have some after the test.

363
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:38,460
Everything good
will be sold out by then.

364
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:42,440
If the good ones are gone,
there're always better ones.

365
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:43,840
See?

366
00:21:44,668 --> 00:21:47,074
It's this late at night,
and people are still selling food.

367
00:21:47,890 --> 00:21:49,268
Tomorrow when you're done,

368
00:21:49,292 --> 00:21:51,559
why wouldn't
there be anything left?

369
00:21:51,584 --> 00:21:53,240
Fine. Okay.

370
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:03,720
Easy now, don't rush.

371
00:22:03,744 --> 00:22:06,130
- You're old, act like it.
- I'm fine, I'm fine.

372
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,920
"If we move over there,"

373
00:22:13,533 --> 00:22:16,680
"worst case, we'll have to stock
the fridge with lots of food."

374
00:22:29,053 --> 00:22:33,700
"It happens at
an all-girls high school."

375
00:22:42,235 --> 00:22:44,581
"Uncle: I'll be home late.
Taking care of a customer."

376
00:22:44,605 --> 00:22:46,781
"Got any work done?"

377
00:22:46,805 --> 00:22:48,901
"Keep at it."

378
00:22:59,436 --> 00:23:01,100
"Improve your English anytime, anywhere."

379
00:23:01,124 --> 00:23:02,750
"Starting at 2,000 THB per month."

380
00:23:02,774 --> 00:23:04,874
"Role-play in real English
with native speakers."

381
00:23:06,768 --> 00:23:08,268
"Apple now."

382
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:29,373
Hey, Moo Krata?
(Thai BBQ hot pot)

383
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,320
Eat up, guys.

384
00:23:37,875 --> 00:23:40,309
- Here.
- Auntie, you eat too.

385
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,813
Look at you.
Grilling like a machine.

386
00:23:50,040 --> 00:23:51,428
Are you grilling to sell?

387
00:23:51,453 --> 00:23:52,896
I'm selling to you all.

388
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:54,936
I know you're stressed.

389
00:23:55,407 --> 00:23:57,763
But you have to eat too.
Don't just grill.

390
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,915
Here. Eat.

391
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:02,575
You don't have to feed me!

392
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:05,040
Take care of your beloved Nidnoi.

393
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:07,369
- I take it then.
- Babe.

394
00:24:07,394 --> 00:24:09,207
- Here, this is for you.
- Put it right here.

395
00:24:09,232 --> 00:24:10,306
Thank you, babe.

396
00:24:10,331 --> 00:24:11,359
Have some veggies too.

397
00:24:11,384 --> 00:24:14,055
- Sure. You eat those too, Auntie.
- Mmhmm.

398
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,821
What's so funny, Mr. Thai?

399
00:24:15,846 --> 00:24:17,905
Well, seeing you
take care of Nidnoi so well,

400
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:20,840
I couldn't help but laugh
about how you two met.

401
00:24:27,425 --> 00:24:28,880
So cringe.

402
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,615
Come to think of it,
looking back now

403
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:35,255
I don't know how
we made it this far either.

404
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:37,295
Let me tell you,
the first day I saw her,

405
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,779
She walked in dressed so neatly.

406
00:24:39,803 --> 00:24:41,293
She was so innocent.

407
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:42,720
She said...

408
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:44,480
"Excuse me,"

409
00:24:45,370 --> 00:24:47,377
"I'm here to ask for
a Transgender Certif— oops..."

410
00:24:47,612 --> 00:24:50,077
"I mean, a Medical Certificate
of Gender Identity, please."

411
00:24:50,102 --> 00:24:51,116
Just like that.

412
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:53,323
You have quite a memory.

413
00:24:53,347 --> 00:24:55,119
Can't you remember
the good stuff instead?

414
00:24:55,143 --> 00:24:58,680
Auntie, stuff like this sticks.

415
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,920
- Oh wow.
- I remember. You were so pure.

416
00:25:00,944 --> 00:25:03,815
Short hair, buttoned-up shirt.

417
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:05,640
Ooh... I was so confused.

418
00:25:05,664 --> 00:25:08,895
I told her to go home.
Dress how she want to dress.

419
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:12,440
Be herself.
Otherwise, she wouldn't pass.

420
00:25:15,958 --> 00:25:20,600
So cute. So adorable. So pure.

421
00:25:22,102 --> 00:25:25,008
Thank you for taking care
of me all this time.

422
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:31,048
Ugh... you two need to
hurry up and go to Canada already.

423
00:25:31,073 --> 00:25:32,073
I'm jealous.

424
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:35,720
Please let my visa get approved.

425
00:25:36,631 --> 00:25:38,960
The embassy just asked for
more documents the other day.

426
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:39,960
What?

427
00:25:40,808 --> 00:25:43,781
I told you we should get married.
Then we could go as spouses.

428
00:25:44,809 --> 00:25:45,875
Let's do it tomorrow.

429
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:47,851
- Ooh!
- Congratulations in advance!

430
00:25:48,210 --> 00:25:49,920
You two are my witnesses.

431
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:54,280
Aren't you going to check
for an auspicious date?

432
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:56,440
You never miss stuff like that.

433
00:25:56,913 --> 00:25:59,335
For this, I'm using the
Auspicious Time of Convenience.

434
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,640
Because either way,
Nidnoi and I are solid.

435
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:05,615
Signing or no signing,
ceremony or no ceremony.

436
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:07,157
I don't care about that anyway.

437
00:26:07,182 --> 00:26:10,065
I think you'll pass for sure.

438
00:26:10,089 --> 00:26:12,105
You're worrying about nothing.

439
00:26:12,130 --> 00:26:13,203
Hey, let's do this.

440
00:26:14,645 --> 00:26:18,027
Congratulations in advance
to both of my friends.

441
00:26:18,052 --> 00:26:19,052
- Yay!
- Yay!

442
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:21,495
Thank you so much, Mr. Thai.

443
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:22,680
May your words come true.

444
00:26:23,946 --> 00:26:25,660
By the way...

445
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:31,760
If Ohn decides to move
to Singapore with Jee,

446
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,920
that leaves you here all alone.

447
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:38,880
To put our minds at ease, Thai,

448
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:41,466
when are you going
to have someone?

449
00:26:47,253 --> 00:26:48,600
I choose not to have anyone.

450
00:26:49,639 --> 00:26:50,840
I choose to be alone.

451
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:55,346
Do I have any love interest? Yes.

452
00:26:55,725 --> 00:26:56,725
But...

453
00:26:57,670 --> 00:26:59,491
I don't want to get physical.

454
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,720
I don't want any attachments.

455
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:05,720
But don't you worry.
I can take care of myself.

456
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:09,468
I've already planned out
my future for when I'm old.

457
00:27:09,493 --> 00:27:11,080
And right now, I'm fine.

458
00:27:11,439 --> 00:27:14,658
As for you guys,
you can go wherever you want.

459
00:27:15,935 --> 00:27:17,715
When Kit's anniversary comes around

460
00:27:17,739 --> 00:27:19,739
I'll go myself. I'll go alone.

461
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:21,440
Mr. Confident.

462
00:27:21,700 --> 00:27:22,720
Yeah.

463
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,040
Hey, I almost forgot.

464
00:27:25,533 --> 00:27:26,533
What?

465
00:27:26,558 --> 00:27:27,998
I got news about Mae Champi.

466
00:27:33,177 --> 00:27:34,177
Queen.

467
00:27:35,978 --> 00:27:37,018
Yes?

468
00:27:37,042 --> 00:27:38,096
"Mae Champi"

469
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:42,254
My intel says
she's very sick right now.

470
00:27:42,279 --> 00:27:44,535
And she's taking care
of herself all alone.

471
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:46,356
Should we make
a plan to go visit her?

472
00:27:46,381 --> 00:27:47,657
- Mmm.
- Let's do it.

473
00:27:47,681 --> 00:27:49,771
Don't wait too long.
Or we won't make it in time.

474
00:27:49,771 --> 00:27:50,774
If she...

475
00:27:50,799 --> 00:27:51,799
- Thai!
- Thai!

476
00:27:53,349 --> 00:27:55,720
Okay. Scratch that.

477
00:27:57,240 --> 00:28:00,726
Let's meet up soon.
Before Chon and Nidnoi travel.

478
00:28:00,751 --> 00:28:04,413
Let's say before the comic artist

479
00:28:04,438 --> 00:28:07,416
moves to Singapore to follow Jee.

480
00:28:08,505 --> 00:28:09,720
Okay. Deal.

481
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:13,400
- Cheers... come on, cheers!
- Yay!

482
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,080
You eat too, Auntie.

483
00:28:18,105 --> 00:28:19,105
Yeah.

484
00:28:21,194 --> 00:28:22,440
Ooh-ho!

485
00:28:22,464 --> 00:28:23,553
Wow.

486
00:28:27,204 --> 00:28:28,644
Look yummy.

487
00:28:28,889 --> 00:28:30,400
Mmm. Looks good, doesn't it?

488
00:28:30,872 --> 00:28:31,920
Looks very good.

489
00:28:31,944 --> 00:28:33,200
"Be my guest."

490
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:36,432
"This is roast duck."

491
00:28:36,457 --> 00:28:37,720
- Thank you.
- Here.

492
00:28:38,372 --> 00:28:39,720
And another one here.

493
00:28:40,252 --> 00:28:41,365
Lovely.

494
00:28:41,638 --> 00:28:42,880
Wow.

495
00:28:43,737 --> 00:28:45,066
Thank you.

496
00:28:45,091 --> 00:28:46,091
Please, please.

497
00:28:50,536 --> 00:28:51,536
Great.

498
00:28:57,479 --> 00:29:00,665
Thank you, thank you,
thank you, Jira.

499
00:29:01,739 --> 00:29:03,408
Food is so delicious.

500
00:29:03,433 --> 00:29:05,330
- Oh!
- They are yummy.

501
00:29:06,158 --> 00:29:07,640
Everything is good.

502
00:29:07,957 --> 00:29:09,237
My pleasure.

503
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:10,848
Oh...

504
00:29:10,873 --> 00:29:14,302
If I were you, I can't image myself

505
00:29:14,327 --> 00:29:17,075
living with this food paradise.

506
00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:18,200
Oh.

507
00:29:18,224 --> 00:29:22,994
Actually, Singapore
has Hawker food centers.

508
00:29:23,019 --> 00:29:26,000
Cheap prices,
but excellent management.

509
00:29:26,024 --> 00:29:28,024
Unlike the street food here,

510
00:29:28,032 --> 00:29:30,590
which needs a lot of improvement.

511
00:29:31,560 --> 00:29:35,960
I think every place has
its good and bad points.

512
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,000
Mmm.

513
00:29:37,025 --> 00:29:39,326
But where your heart is,

514
00:29:39,936 --> 00:29:41,610
that is your home.

515
00:29:41,634 --> 00:29:43,172
Yes, that's true.

516
00:29:43,196 --> 00:29:45,840
No matter where your heart is

517
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:48,040
that place is your home.

518
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,160
And I hope

519
00:29:52,110 --> 00:29:53,160
Singapore

520
00:29:54,152 --> 00:29:56,320
will be a new home for you.

521
00:29:57,996 --> 00:29:58,996
Oh!

522
00:30:01,653 --> 00:30:04,109
Please consider your contract.

523
00:30:07,973 --> 00:30:08,974
Wow.

524
00:30:09,830 --> 00:30:10,834
Oh.

525
00:30:11,284 --> 00:30:13,256
Thank you very much indeed.

526
00:30:14,411 --> 00:30:18,976
Give me your answer
as soon as possible.

527
00:30:19,001 --> 00:30:21,814
ASAP. As soon as possible.

528
00:30:23,475 --> 00:30:24,610
Oh, right.

529
00:30:24,635 --> 00:30:25,722
One thing.

530
00:30:26,310 --> 00:30:28,463
I think I'm free tonight.

531
00:30:29,093 --> 00:30:32,579
Oh, I think
I do have a plan for you.

532
00:30:32,764 --> 00:30:33,781
Good.

533
00:30:46,666 --> 00:30:47,800
Awesome!

534
00:30:48,807 --> 00:30:50,667
♪ Listen to your heart ♪

535
00:30:50,692 --> 00:30:52,713
♪ Tell me who you want to be ♪

536
00:30:52,738 --> 00:30:54,596
♪ We can always start ♪

537
00:30:54,621 --> 00:30:56,440
♪ Start to believe ♪

538
00:30:56,465 --> 00:30:58,463
♪ Listen to your heart ♪

539
00:30:58,488 --> 00:31:01,182
♪ Tell me that you understand ♪

540
00:31:01,207 --> 00:31:03,760
♪ Cuz you are the one for me ♪

541
00:31:10,984 --> 00:31:13,143
♪ You are the one for me ♪

542
00:31:14,721 --> 00:31:17,040
Woo!

543
00:31:17,064 --> 00:31:18,440
Woo hoo!

544
00:31:18,657 --> 00:31:20,720
♪ You are the one for me ♪

545
00:31:21,712 --> 00:31:22,720
Cheers!

546
00:31:24,397 --> 00:31:27,530
This is absolutely amazing, Jira.

547
00:31:28,753 --> 00:31:31,043
This is a truely work of art.

548
00:31:31,359 --> 00:31:32,372
Oh...

549
00:31:32,597 --> 00:31:34,597
I'm glad you like this.

550
00:31:34,874 --> 00:31:37,040
♪ You are the one for me ♪

551
00:31:37,877 --> 00:31:39,297
I envy you.

552
00:31:39,321 --> 00:31:40,800
Envy me of what?

553
00:31:40,824 --> 00:31:42,079
I'm so envious.

554
00:31:42,104 --> 00:31:43,104
Envious of what?

555
00:31:43,549 --> 00:31:46,200
I wish I had this kind
of freedom every day.

556
00:32:06,121 --> 00:32:07,126
Hmm?

557
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,160
You're back, Ohn?

558
00:32:09,497 --> 00:32:10,550
Yep.

559
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,421
Wait. Hey!

560
00:32:19,446 --> 00:32:21,081
I'm getting soaked!

561
00:32:21,106 --> 00:32:22,126
Shower with me.

562
00:32:23,746 --> 00:32:24,936
But I'm tired.

563
00:32:24,961 --> 00:32:26,455
Mmm...

564
00:32:29,479 --> 00:32:31,360
Then I'll scrub your back for you.

565
00:32:34,311 --> 00:32:36,686
Wait. Calm down, Jee.

566
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:38,920
You prepared for this?

567
00:32:39,313 --> 00:32:40,313
Mmm.

568
00:32:41,289 --> 00:32:42,600
Let's shower together.

569
00:32:44,648 --> 00:32:46,314
Wait, Jee.

570
00:32:46,338 --> 00:32:48,304
I still have my clothes on.

571
00:32:48,329 --> 00:32:49,544
Let me.

572
00:32:50,219 --> 00:32:52,880
Jee, you're crazy. That tickles!

573
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,320
I'll do it myself!

574
00:32:55,835 --> 00:32:56,880
It's good.

575
00:32:57,196 --> 00:32:58,196
But it's a no.

576
00:32:59,868 --> 00:33:01,520
Huh? Why?

577
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,782
Didn't you say...

578
00:33:04,807 --> 00:33:06,847
you wanted a story similar to

579
00:33:06,871 --> 00:33:08,871
The Sorceress of
the Enchanted City?

580
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:14,800
Similar in terms of
popularity and hype.

581
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:19,304
But nobody reads
Kittima the Sorceress anymore

582
00:33:19,329 --> 00:33:21,323
I want something...

583
00:33:21,348 --> 00:33:24,240
Fresh. New. A smash hit.

584
00:33:27,392 --> 00:33:28,392
Ohn...

585
00:33:28,868 --> 00:33:31,560
Please, help me find
a new door to open.

586
00:33:32,376 --> 00:33:35,975
But what I pitched
is a sequel to Kittima.

587
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,815
The fans will definitely buy it.

588
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:42,200
We can focus on
the original fanbase first, right?

589
00:33:50,496 --> 00:33:51,800
Liu, I'll call you back.

590
00:33:53,501 --> 00:33:54,600
Go on, Ohn.

591
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:58,166
Kittima ended with...

592
00:33:58,191 --> 00:34:00,775
her never returning
to the human world again.

593
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:04,360
But if we do a sequel,
we'll get the original readers,

594
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:09,695
who want to know what happened to
the first love Kittima left behind.

595
00:34:09,720 --> 00:34:12,960
And if Kittima returns to
the human world once more

596
00:34:12,985 --> 00:34:14,585
with magical powers

597
00:34:14,609 --> 00:34:17,038
and brutal demons chasing after her.

598
00:34:17,063 --> 00:34:19,120
Can't we really sell that?

599
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:21,320
That's the risk, Ohn.

600
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:27,055
And the international market is
another big opportunity, you know?

601
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:29,707
That's why I want
something that excites people,

602
00:34:29,731 --> 00:34:32,295
no matter where they're from.

603
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:35,863
And one thing is for sure,
we are not doing the sequel.

604
00:34:36,610 --> 00:34:40,583
Because the new customers
we want to capture,

605
00:34:41,300 --> 00:34:42,963
nobody knows Kittima anymore.

606
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:46,330
Kittima is history.

607
00:34:47,240 --> 00:34:48,640
Don't try to resurrect it.

608
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:54,960
Mmm.

609
00:34:58,631 --> 00:34:59,880
Liu...

610
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:04,440
Hello.

611
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:07,080
Sorry.

612
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:11,760
I can talk now. Not busy anymore.

613
00:35:18,336 --> 00:35:19,440
Yes, dear, yes.

614
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:23,320
Sure.

615
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:27,440
Don't be mad at me, Liu.

616
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,240
I was busy.

617
00:35:33,887 --> 00:35:34,888
Okay...

618
00:35:34,913 --> 00:35:36,690
A touch-up?

619
00:35:36,715 --> 00:35:40,320
Mmm, time to take care of Duckman.

620
00:35:42,247 --> 00:35:47,130
Alright. I miss Duckman.

621
00:35:48,835 --> 00:35:49,835
Um...

622
00:35:50,644 --> 00:35:56,049
Thank you for
taking care of my tattoo.

623
00:35:57,073 --> 00:36:00,716
No problem.
I'm very happy you like it.

624
00:36:01,474 --> 00:36:03,360
Um...

625
00:36:03,604 --> 00:36:06,563
How old is this tattoo?

626
00:36:06,588 --> 00:36:07,608
Say what?

627
00:36:08,169 --> 00:36:10,916
How old is this tattoo?

628
00:36:11,655 --> 00:36:13,062
Um...

629
00:36:13,087 --> 00:36:18,287
Oh. How old...

630
00:36:18,923 --> 00:36:20,697
Chon!

631
00:36:20,721 --> 00:36:22,434
You're the one
who tattooed this on me!

632
00:36:22,458 --> 00:36:23,556
Don't you remember?

633
00:36:23,581 --> 00:36:24,868
Why are you asking me?

634
00:36:24,893 --> 00:36:26,853
I thought you wanted
to practice speaking English.

635
00:36:26,878 --> 00:36:28,080
I was speaking English to you!

636
00:36:28,183 --> 00:36:29,289
Ugh!

637
00:36:29,313 --> 00:36:32,567
Enough of that. I want to chat.

638
00:36:32,592 --> 00:36:34,398
Fine. Let's speak Thai.

639
00:36:34,423 --> 00:36:36,280
- More fun to gossip in Thai.
- Mmm.

640
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:41,910
Being 54...

641
00:36:43,537 --> 00:36:45,850
It's not easy at all.
Don't you think?

642
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:50,063
Any idea that I think is cool...

643
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:51,560
It's just...

644
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:54,943
It doesn't seem cool or fit
with these days anymore.

645
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:56,960
They act like...

646
00:36:57,626 --> 00:36:59,996
I'm not even living
in the same era as them.

647
00:37:01,182 --> 00:37:04,683
I'm just barely older than them.

648
00:37:05,916 --> 00:37:07,496
Oh, please.

649
00:37:08,327 --> 00:37:10,496
Has life ever been easy?

650
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:13,610
It's hard at every age.

651
00:37:14,840 --> 00:37:16,408
Being a teenager is hard.

652
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:18,641
Being an adult is hard.

653
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,175
Being our age is hard.

654
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:23,915
If we live longer,

655
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:26,280
it'll just be
hard for longer, right?

656
00:37:28,187 --> 00:37:30,523
Hmm. You're right.

657
00:37:33,240 --> 00:37:37,023
♪ Life isn't as hard as you think ♪

658
00:37:37,512 --> 00:37:41,448
♪ But life isn't easy at all ♪

659
00:37:41,473 --> 00:37:42,880
- Chon.
- What?

660
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:44,366
- Is that how it goes?
- I don't know.

661
00:37:44,391 --> 00:37:45,434
You sang it backwards.

662
00:37:45,434 --> 00:37:46,790
- Really?
- It goes like this.

663
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:52,320
♪ Life isn't easy at all ♪

664
00:37:54,035 --> 00:37:57,956
♪ Life isn't as hard as you think ♪

665
00:37:59,473 --> 00:38:01,479
It's a rock song. I remember.

666
00:38:01,504 --> 00:38:02,717
Sure, whatever.

667
00:38:03,580 --> 00:38:05,259
So, where are we
on the Singapore thing?

668
00:38:06,727 --> 00:38:08,007
I'm still not sure.

669
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:11,531
But Jee seems to really want to go.

670
00:38:11,556 --> 00:38:12,558
Mmm.

671
00:38:13,704 --> 00:38:15,816
I don't want to let him go alone.

672
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:18,880
What about you?

673
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:21,910
Do you think you'll get the visa?

674
00:38:27,462 --> 00:38:29,682
Whether I get it or not,
I have to keep going, don't I?

675
00:38:31,888 --> 00:38:33,848
But I feel discouraged
whenever I think about it.

676
00:38:35,875 --> 00:38:38,655
I'm starting to feel
too lazy to move.

677
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,520
Hey, don't say that.

678
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:43,840
Calm down.
Get a hold of yourself.

679
00:38:43,865 --> 00:38:45,343
Take a deep breath.

680
00:38:45,368 --> 00:38:46,531
Breathe in deep.

681
00:38:46,556 --> 00:38:48,280
Breathe out long.

682
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,680
Breathe in deep.

683
00:38:50,191 --> 00:38:51,721
Breathe out long.

684
00:38:51,746 --> 00:38:52,920
Just like that.

685
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:57,975
You and Nidnoi have come
more than halfway already.

686
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:59,720
You still have months to prepare.

687
00:39:00,226 --> 00:39:01,799
Are you really going
to dump it all now?

688
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:04,770
I'm not dumping it, just venting.

689
00:39:05,255 --> 00:39:07,283
Me and Nidnoi are committed.

690
00:39:07,308 --> 00:39:09,136
No matter what, we won't bail.

691
00:39:09,850 --> 00:39:13,416
For us, to get to this point,

692
00:39:14,022 --> 00:39:16,916
we've been through a lot together.
How could we bail?

693
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,760
Mmm. Exactly.

694
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:23,923
So, have you guys
registered the marriage yet?

695
00:39:25,252 --> 00:39:28,934
I plan to wait and see
about the visa first.

696
00:39:28,934 --> 00:39:30,452
If it doesn't work out,

697
00:39:30,476 --> 00:39:32,823
then I'll seriously
think about registering.

698
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:37,529
Alright. I'll be waiting
to be your witness.

699
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:39,080
Great.

700
00:39:39,434 --> 00:39:42,304
Oh, Ohn. Hello.

701
00:39:42,304 --> 00:39:44,023
- Hello.
- You're back.

702
00:39:44,304 --> 00:39:45,976
- Getting a touch-up?
- Yep.

703
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:51,520
Seeing her happy makes me okay.

704
00:40:03,805 --> 00:40:05,775
"The love between Nidnoi and Chon"

705
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,600
"might confuse some people."

706
00:40:08,312 --> 00:40:11,080
"Because they don't know
how to classify Chon or Nidnoi."

707
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:13,095
"What label to put on them?"

708
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,267
"After all,"

709
00:40:14,291 --> 00:40:17,933
"it's more than just a love
between a man and a woman."

710
00:40:19,170 --> 00:40:21,455
"In a time when
people didn't understand"

711
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:23,975
"Nidnoi and Chon
overcame so many obstacles."

712
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:27,673
"Family, friends,
and even themselves."

713
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:31,249
"But in the end... Love Wins."

714
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:33,483
"When you find true love,"

715
00:40:33,507 --> 00:40:36,295
why cares who the other person is
or what gender they are?"

716
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:37,533
"It's just love."

717
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:40,756
"I'm so jealous!"

718
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:45,880
"Get your comic plot approved,
then follow me to Singapore, okay?"

719
00:40:47,282 --> 00:40:49,219
"Jee... Jee, don't leave me."

720
00:40:49,244 --> 00:40:52,520
"Jee.. Jee! Don't leave me!"

721
00:41:16,856 --> 00:41:17,856
Oh.

722
00:41:18,879 --> 00:41:19,880
Jee.

723
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:22,600
You came in so quietly.
Have you eaten yet?

724
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:25,280
Mmm. What about you?

725
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:31,920
I already had Som Tum
with Chon and Nidnoi.

726
00:41:33,520 --> 00:41:34,520
Well...

727
00:41:35,608 --> 00:41:36,608
Yeah?

728
00:41:38,679 --> 00:41:40,640
Want to do your nails?
I'll do them for you.

729
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,680
Hmm?

730
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:46,600
You're in a pampering mood today.

731
00:41:53,277 --> 00:41:54,486
Oh.

732
00:41:56,274 --> 00:41:57,474
Just a sec.

733
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:01,480
Hello, Aom.

734
00:42:21,712 --> 00:42:24,760
What time are you taking Mom
to the hospital tomorrow?

735
00:42:26,399 --> 00:42:28,360
That early?

736
00:42:29,574 --> 00:42:31,880
Oh, right. She has a blood test.

737
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:37,440
Make sure she fasts.
No food or water before she goes.

738
00:42:41,303 --> 00:42:42,324
Last time,

739
00:42:42,349 --> 00:42:44,695
her blood sugar was so high.

740
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:46,080
The doctor even scolded her.

741
00:42:48,181 --> 00:42:49,320
Um-hmm.

742
00:42:52,040 --> 00:42:53,520
Hey, listen.

743
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:57,784
About Singapore,
don't tell Mom yet, okay?

744
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,000
Mmm.

745
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:03,826
Okay?

746
00:43:14,099 --> 00:43:19,046
So, who said they were
going to do my nails?

747
00:43:19,071 --> 00:43:20,072
Hmm?

748
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:35,866
Wait, Jee.

749
00:43:35,891 --> 00:43:37,160
Jee...

750
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:39,640
Oh, Jee...

751
00:43:41,932 --> 00:43:43,215
Just a sec.

752
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:44,840
See?

753
00:43:44,864 --> 00:43:46,634
I knew it.

754
00:43:46,659 --> 00:43:48,560
Coming in all sweet
and pampering like this.

755
00:43:49,253 --> 00:43:51,816
You're up to no good, don't you?

756
00:43:53,800 --> 00:43:55,203
I do understand you.

757
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:57,743
Having a boyfriend as cute as me

758
00:43:57,767 --> 00:43:59,767
makes it hard
to control yourself, right?

759
00:44:00,273 --> 00:44:01,273
Mmm.

760
00:44:01,776 --> 00:44:05,063
What's wrong?
Don't get dramatic on me now.

761
00:44:06,491 --> 00:44:09,276
You can't distract me.

762
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:12,216
I have to practice English.

763
00:44:14,450 --> 00:44:17,716
"I go to bathroom. Shower."

764
00:44:17,741 --> 00:44:20,490
"I want to practice English, okay?"

765
00:44:27,325 --> 00:44:31,323
"I need spicy food, please!"

766
00:44:51,768 --> 00:44:53,108
"Gotta fight!"

767
00:45:11,152 --> 00:45:12,152
Umm. Jee.

768
00:45:12,177 --> 00:45:13,177
Hmm?

769
00:45:14,957 --> 00:45:16,880
The new comic project turns out...

770
00:45:18,120 --> 00:45:19,823
the editor wasn't interested.

771
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:25,356
So, nothing left to worry about.

772
00:45:26,560 --> 00:45:27,560
Oh.

773
00:45:35,937 --> 00:45:36,942
Umm.

774
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:41,720
I think if I move there...

775
00:45:42,775 --> 00:45:46,303
I can still work
drawing novel covers,

776
00:45:46,720 --> 00:45:48,996
illustrations or whatever.

777
00:45:50,280 --> 00:45:53,080
If they don't use AI
to draw it instead.

778
00:46:00,359 --> 00:46:01,759
I want to talk to you.

779
00:46:05,244 --> 00:46:06,753
About Singapore, right?

780
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:34,283
Come with me.

781
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:36,920
Go where?

782
00:46:38,930 --> 00:46:40,120
To live in Singapore.

783
00:47:05,623 --> 00:47:08,364
- I won't go to Singapore anymore.
- I will go to Singapore with you.

784
00:47:08,389 --> 00:47:10,160
- Huh? Why?
- Huh? Why?

785
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,380
Jee...

786
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:16,693
You want to go to Singapore.

787
00:47:17,498 --> 00:47:19,280
I can move there with you.

788
00:47:20,240 --> 00:47:24,120
Just give me some time
to clear up my life here first.

789
00:47:25,680 --> 00:47:28,440
Give me time to get a new passport.

790
00:47:29,120 --> 00:47:30,386
Clear up my work.

791
00:47:31,229 --> 00:47:32,535
Go home to tell Mom.

792
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:35,335
No, Ohn. We don't have to
go to Singapore anymore.

793
00:47:35,360 --> 00:47:38,160
Don't just give up like this, Jee.

794
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:40,895
Why the sudden change of heart?

795
00:47:40,920 --> 00:47:43,210
You've wanted to go all along.

796
00:47:43,708 --> 00:47:46,480
Because I know you're
just going along with me

797
00:47:46,480 --> 00:47:48,720
even though you really
don't want to go at all.

798
00:47:50,400 --> 00:47:53,200
I admit, I'm just following you.

799
00:47:53,994 --> 00:47:55,720
- Mmm.
- But...

800
00:47:57,736 --> 00:47:59,510
I don't want to break up with you.

801
00:48:01,739 --> 00:48:02,816
How about this?

802
00:48:03,760 --> 00:48:06,280
You go work over there.

803
00:48:07,320 --> 00:48:10,480
We try living apart for a while.

804
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:14,840
A long-distance relationship?

805
00:48:14,840 --> 00:48:15,840
Mmm.

806
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:19,240
I've thought about that too.

807
00:48:21,358 --> 00:48:23,160
But no. Better not separate.

808
00:48:24,053 --> 00:48:26,520
Neither of us are young anymore.

809
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:30,687
Starting over with housing
and work is difficult enough.

810
00:48:30,712 --> 00:48:33,240
On top of that having
a long-distance relationship?

811
00:48:33,265 --> 00:48:35,680
Oh boy, that's exhausting.

812
00:48:39,360 --> 00:48:40,360
Jee...

813
00:48:41,431 --> 00:48:42,800
You really are old, aren't you?

814
00:48:43,720 --> 00:48:47,200
These days, you don't dare to
challenge yourself like before.

815
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:50,920
Oh please.
Like you're any different.

816
00:48:50,920 --> 00:48:53,541
Sneaking off to learn English.
Haven't seen you get very far.

817
00:48:53,566 --> 00:48:55,405
That definitely is old.

818
00:48:55,890 --> 00:48:59,717
Nothing new sticks
in the brain anymore.

819
00:48:59,742 --> 00:49:01,640
Hey!

820
00:49:02,359 --> 00:49:05,200
I just want to be with you.

821
00:49:08,491 --> 00:49:12,836
So I took online English classes.

822
00:49:13,320 --> 00:49:16,120
And I went to check my horoscope.

823
00:49:16,144 --> 00:49:18,800
I've been going on
in circles all week

824
00:49:18,800 --> 00:49:24,005
about Mom, myself.
and what to do with my life.

825
00:49:25,755 --> 00:49:29,113
I know. That's why
we have to be together.

826
00:49:29,138 --> 00:49:30,535
To figure things out together.

827
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:33,400
Won't you regret the job?

828
00:49:36,840 --> 00:49:41,680
The only thing I'll regret is
probably the later retirement age.

829
00:49:42,600 --> 00:49:45,303
But truthfully, I don't want to
work until I'm 65 or 70 anyway.

830
00:49:45,960 --> 00:49:47,320
Assuming I even live that long.

831
00:49:48,200 --> 00:49:51,440
Come to think of it,
at 60, I'll still have energy.

832
00:49:51,440 --> 00:49:53,793
I'll want to do things
I've never done before, you know?

833
00:50:00,028 --> 00:50:01,280
You understand me, right?

834
00:50:26,119 --> 00:50:27,119
Jee…

835
00:50:28,467 --> 00:50:29,467
Hmm?

836
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:33,120
We aren't moving
to Singapore anymore, right?

837
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:34,680
Mmm.

838
00:50:35,840 --> 00:50:36,840
Hey.

839
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:38,480
What?

840
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:42,923
But are we still going
on a trip together?

841
00:50:49,688 --> 00:50:50,688
Sure.

842
00:50:55,850 --> 00:50:56,855
Night night.

843
00:50:56,880 --> 00:50:57,920
Night night.

844
00:50:58,665 --> 00:50:59,712
But...

845
00:51:01,277 --> 00:51:03,495
Don't snore in my ear, okay?

846
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:06,200
Mmm... Okay.

847
00:51:07,961 --> 00:51:09,476
I'll do something else instead.

848
00:51:09,501 --> 00:51:11,076
- Take that.
- Hey! Hey!

849
00:51:11,101 --> 00:51:12,328
Jee. You're crazy. Stop!

850
00:51:12,352 --> 00:51:14,960
Jee... Jee... Stop it, Jee!

851
00:51:15,672 --> 00:51:18,360
"The plan to move to Singapore
has officially collapsed."

852
00:51:19,080 --> 00:51:22,575
"But the 'Don't Break Up in
the 7th Year' project is still on."

853
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:24,026
"We have to dethrone"

854
00:51:24,051 --> 00:51:26,403
"the reigning champions
of sweetness, Chon and Nidnoi."

855
00:51:42,223 --> 00:51:46,415
"What I didn't tell Ohn is
that I would be heartbroken"

856
00:51:46,440 --> 00:51:48,440
"if he didn't have
the people he loves"

857
00:51:48,465 --> 00:51:51,855
"to talk to about
everything and nothing."

858
00:51:51,880 --> 00:51:54,900
"Even if some of his friends
choose to be alone"

859
00:51:54,900 --> 00:51:57,010
"but don't feel lonely."

860
00:51:57,674 --> 00:52:01,895
"Or how some friends
might be moving away soon"

861
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:04,750
"even if they're facing
a lot of obstacles right now."

862
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:09,535
"Tonight, I hope everyone
can put their minds at ease"

863
00:52:09,560 --> 00:52:11,720
"and fall asleep with hope."

864
00:52:14,912 --> 00:52:18,708
"Oh man, I don't think
I can sleep tonight."

865
00:52:18,733 --> 00:52:20,846
"Should I move to Singapore
to sleep after all."

866
00:53:35,232 --> 00:53:37,467
"I can't sleep tonight"

867
00:53:37,492 --> 00:53:39,398
"because I dragged
myself out of bed"

868
00:53:39,422 --> 00:53:41,422
"to build a blog for my boyfriend."

869
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:50,760
This Saturday,
let's go to my house again.

870
00:53:51,399 --> 00:53:52,399
It's Mom's birthday.

871
00:53:54,266 --> 00:53:56,036
Does your mom really want me to go?

872
00:53:56,441 --> 00:53:58,143
Can you not bring Ohn?

873
00:53:58,360 --> 00:54:00,240
I'm afraid Mom will be embarrassed.

874
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:04,520
I'll try not to overthink it.

875
00:54:04,545 --> 00:54:07,735
If Jee is really flirting
with that kid in Room 405,

876
00:54:07,760 --> 00:54:09,190
he wouldn't tell me, right?

877
00:54:09,877 --> 00:54:12,760
Hey, Fabs! Come here!

878
00:54:13,600 --> 00:54:17,320
She probably get good energy
from people she trusts like us.

879
00:54:22,441 --> 00:54:27,320
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

880
00:54:27,320 --> 00:54:33,360
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

881
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:39,011
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

882
00:54:39,036 --> 00:54:42,215
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

883
00:54:42,240 --> 00:54:47,480
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

884
00:54:47,480 --> 00:54:53,720
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

885
00:54:53,720 --> 00:54:59,120
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

886
00:54:59,685 --> 00:55:03,960
♪ Every day together
just you and I ♪

887
00:55:03,960 --> 00:55:08,680
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

888
00:55:09,160 --> 00:55:14,000
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

889
00:55:14,000 --> 00:55:18,520
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

890
00:55:19,024 --> 00:55:24,000
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

891
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:28,512
♪ La la la la la la la ♪
